  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/5100",
  "title": "Inserting an InsightsMiddleware before widgets results in urlSynced-state being cleared on reload",
  "body": "## 🐛 Bug description\r\n\r\nWhen we `createInsightsMiddleware` and insert that component before other widgets in an `<InstantSearch>` page, any state that is in urlSync gets erased on page load (such as pressing Enter or navigating from another page).\r\nCC @Haroenv with whom I discovered the root cause of the UI issue.\r\n\r\n## 🔍 Bug reproduction\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n1. Create an insights middleware that sets some stuff\r\n2. Insert it in your `<InstantSearch routing={true}>` page _before other widgets_ (such as `<RefinementList>`)\r\n3. Click a filter to set some `urlSync`-ed parameters in the URL\r\n4. Click on your URL and press enter\r\n5. See the page reloading: the url is first kept, then erased during a second painting of the page\r\n\r\n## :curly_loop: Workaround\r\n\r\nWe realized that changing the position of the middleware in the DOM, from:\r\n```jsx\r\n<InstantSearch>\r\n  <InsightsMiddleware />\r\n  <RefinementList />\r\n  <Hits />\r\n</InstantSearch>\r\n```\r\nto\r\n```jsx\r\n<InstantSearch>\r\n  <RefinementList />\r\n  <Hits />\r\n  <InsightsMiddleware />\r\n</InstantSearch>\r\n```\r\nis enough to workaround the race condition between the middleware and the other widgets. :thinking: \r\n\r\n**Live reproduction:**\r\n\r\nhttps://codesandbox.io/s/nameless-forest-chr25g?file=/App.tsx\r\n\r\n## 💭 Expected behavior\r\n\r\nI'd expect the middleware to not clear the other widgets' state, _regardless of where it is inserted_.",
